The amount was $1466.85, and I completed the payment on June 22, 2025. Unfortunately, after I sent the money, the seller stopped responding, and I never received the phone. I don't have an email for the seller. They only contacted me through Carousell, and once I paid, they went silent. That’s all I recall about the contact details.

query: I need to report a scam. It happened over a call and then continued on WhatsApp. A person pretended to be from the Ministry of Manpower and scared me about work permits. The person I spoke to was named James Wong, claiming to be from the Ministry of Manpower. After my initial denial, the call was transferred to someone named Inspector Timothy Lee from the Singapore Police Force over WhatsApp. I was scared, and they told me to transfer money for an investigation. The phone number they used was +6591197935. There wasn’t any email involved, just calls and messages. During the call, they claimed there were work permit violations under my name and made it sound very urgent. They didn’t ask for specific documents, but they pressured me into making a transaction to a bank account to "support the investigations." It felt very real at the moment because of their convincing approach, especially since they mentioned government affiliations. The scammer went by the name James Wong on the call, and then later, I was communicating with someone called Inspector Timothy Lee on WhatsApp. I was instructed to transfer money to a Trust account, the identifier was 28327648. They said it was to support their investigations, which added to my fear and urgency. I lost $39,695.01 during this incident. It was a significant amount, and I genuinely believed I was helping with an investigation because of the pressure they applied throughout the communications.
